                                "text": " (I think this is what he's saying) that if you design for neuro-atypical folk (like me) who have immense difficulty getting into a flow state and are easily distracted (I have OCD, misophonia, etc, etc), then you benefit everyone. This is a principle I've always espoused: design for those with disabilities and everyone benefits. I often take the ramp not the stairs in honour of this! I have lever-handled taps in preference to grab-and-turn ones. Mind you, I also have a daughter with disabilities."
